abstract: SUICIDE AT GREENPORT L.I.--George Merrill, a young man about twenty years of age, committed suicide on Monday, at Greenport, by cutting his throat with a razor. The deed was done in the garden, adjoining his father's house. When discovered, fifteen minutes after leaving the house, he was lying on his face, with the open razor in his right hand. The wound was a short one, but deep, immediately above the breast bone.
